    <div class="auction-description">
      <h2>Skills</h2>
      Backbone.js, Chai, Mocha, Node.js, and Sails.js
      <p>As an applicant for an opportunity, I want to understand my eligibility before I apply, so that I don&#39;t apply for opportunities I&#39;m not eligible to work on.</p>

<p><strong>Scenario: Applicant to full time detail sees appropriate eligibility message in confirmation box</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Given I&#39;m a registered user</li>
<li>And there is a full time detail opportunity</li>
<li>When I&#39;ve click on the &quot;I&#39;m In&quot; button on the show page for that opportunity (<a href="https://openopps-staging.18f.gov/tasks/%5Bid%5D">https://openopps-staging.18f.gov/tasks/[id]</a>)</li>
<li>Then an eligibility confirmation box should appear</li>
<li>And the confirmation box should contain the following copy</li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
<p><strong>Are you eligible to participate?</strong></p>

<p><strong>Supervisor Approval</strong>
I have my supervisor&#39;s approval to apply to this opportunity. </p>

<p><strong>Position/ Performance</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>I am a GSA employee serving under a permanent appointment and am at the full performance level of my position.</li>
<li>I have a performance rating of 3 or higher.</li>
<li>I have had no formal, documented disciplinary action within the past year (such as a written warning notice, reprimand, or suspension).
-I am not participating in a different formal development program.
<strong>Location</strong>
If this opportunity is for a specific location (i.e. it is not a virtual opportunity), I am located within the same commuting area.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Grade Level</strong>
If this opportunity is for a specific grade level (i.e. not to unclassified duties), I am at that grade level or higher. </p>
</blockquote>

<p><strong>Scenario: Applicant applies to a non-full time detail opportunity and sees the correct eligibility message</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Given I am a registered user</li>
<li>And there is an opportunity that is NOT a full-time detail</li>
<li>When I click on the &quot;I&#39;m in&quot; button on the show page for that opportunity (<a href="https://openopps-staging.18f.gov/tasks/%5Bid%5D">https://openopps-staging.18f.gov/tasks/[id]</a>)</li>
<li>Then I should see a confirmation box</li>
<li>And that confirmation box should contain the following language</li>
</ul>

<blockquote>
<p><strong>Are you eligible to participate? (all the following should apply)</strong></p>

<ul>
<li><p>I have my supervisor&#39;s approval to apply to this opportunity.</p></li>
<li><p>I am a federal employee (not a contractor).</p></li>
<li><p>If this opportunity is for a specific location (i.e. it is not a virtual opportunity), I am located within the same commuting area.</p></li>
</ul>
</blockquote>

<h2>General acceptance criteria</h2>

<ul>
<li>Test coverage stays the same or increases</li>
<li>Tests pass</li>
<li><strong>A payment URL is specified in your micro-purchase profile so we can pay the award</strong></li>
</ul>

<h2>Notes</h2>

<p>Right now there is just one message for all opportunities. This story is to create one for full-time detail opportunities and one for all other kinds.</p>

<p>The current confirmation box looks like this:
<img src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/100149/18328997/7473ea60-7506-11e6-9d31-d11b7148c175.png" alt="screen shot 2016-09-07 at 2 21 41 pm"></p>

<p>Use the existing styles for both versions. </p>

